## Reading in processed TCGA data

We read in all data, but then filter for only consistent genes that have a FC pvalue <= 0.01.  We also rename the columns for downstream consistency.

```{r tvn}
tvn <- read_csv("tcga-rnaseq-tvn.csv")
tvn <- tvn %>%
mutate(logFC = ifelse(log2FoldChange>=0,2^(abs(log2FoldChange)),-(2^(abs(log2FoldChange))))) %>%
arrange(desc(logFC)) %>%
select(target=GeneId, log2FC.tvn=log2FoldChange, logFC.tvn=logFC, p.tvn=pvalue, fdr.tvn=padj) %>%
filter(fdr.tvn <= tcga.fdr)
```

