## Join mRNA target information

We use the following code to compile TCGA fold change and absolute expression data with the survival data from oncolnc.  We then annotate the data using multiple resources.  The final table will only include genes that are greater than 2-fold deregulated and consistent based on their annotated role, meaning the following:

Oncogenes will have a positive fold change, negative correlation with survival, and the oncogene annotation.

Tumor suppressors will have a negative fold change, positive correlation with survival, and the tumor suppressor annotation.

```{r join}

annot <-  read.csv("annotated_genelist_onctsg.csv") %>%
distinct(target, role)

tvnexp <- left_join(tvn, expr, by="target")
tvnsrv <- left_join(tvnexp, srv, by="target") %>%
left_join(annot, by="target") 

```

#Annotate target genes and filter out genes that do not meet thresholds

```{r filter genes}

if(usefilter == TRUE){
tvnonc <- tvnsrv %>%
  filter(log2FC.tvn >= FCfilter & logHR.srv >= -cox.cutoff & role=="ONC")
tvntsg <- tvnsrv %>%
  filter(log2FC.tvn <= -FCfilter & logHR.srv <= cox.cutoff & role=="TSG")
tvnsrv <- rbind(tvnonc,tvntsg)

}else{
tvnonc <- tvnsrv %>%
  filter(role=="ONC")
tvntsg <- tvnsrv %>%
  filter(role=="TSG")
tvnsrv <- rbind(tvnonc,tvntsg)  
}

write_csv(tvnsrv,paste(outputdir,"/candidategenes.csv",sep = ""))
```

